org.apache.taverna.server.master.interaction

Class InteractionFeedSupport

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.taverna.server.master.interaction.InteractionFeedSupport

  • public class InteractionFeedSupport
extends Object
    Bean that supports interaction feeds. This glues together the Abdera serialization engine and the directory-based model used inside the server.
    Author:
    Donal Fellows

        Gets the contents of a particular feed entry.
        Parameters:
        run - The workflow run that defines which feed we are operating on.
        entryID - The identifier (from the path) of the entry to read.

        The description of the entry.

      • addRunFeedEntry

        public org.apache.abdera.model.Entry addRunFeedEntry(TavernaRun run,
                                                     org.apache.abdera.model.Entry entry)
                                              throws FilesystemAccessException,
                                                     NoDirectoryEntryException,
                                                     NoUpdateException
        Given a partial feed entry, store a complete feed entry in the filesystem for a particular run. Note that this does not permit update of an existing entry; the entry is always created new.
        Parameters:
        run - The workflow run that defines which feed we are operating on.
        entry - The partial entry to store
        Returns:
        A link to the entry.
        Throws:
        FilesystemAccessException - If the entry can't be stored.
        NoDirectoryEntryException - If the run is improperly configured.
        NoUpdateException - If the user isn't allowed to do the write.
        MalformedURLException - If a generated URL is illegal (shouldn't happen).

      • removeRunFeedEntry

        public void removeRunFeedEntry(TavernaRun run,
                               String entryID)
                        throws FilesystemAccessException,
                               NoDirectoryEntryException,
                               NoUpdateException
        Deletes an entry from a feed.
        Parameters:
        run - The workflow run that defines which feed we are operating on.
        entryID - The ID of the entry to delete.
        Throws:
        FilesystemAccessException - If the entry can't be deleted
        NoDirectoryEntryException - If the entry can't be found.
        NoUpdateException - If the current user is not permitted to modify the run's characteristics.
